recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150 vehicles.  Underbody heat and noise insulators may loosen and contact the aluminum driveshaft, which could damage the driveshaft and cause it to fracture.
recalls.Consequence: A fractured driveshaft can cause a loss of drive power, or a loss of vehicle control if the driveshaft contacts the ground.  Additionally, unintended movement could occur while parked if the parking brake is not engaged.  Any of these scenarios can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair the driveshaft as necessary, and properly attach the underbody insulators, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed February 4, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 21S56.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 and 2020-2021 F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 Super Duty vehicles.  During manufacturing, the windshield may not have been properly bonded to the vehicle, allowing it to detach in a crash.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 212, "Windshield Mounting."
recalls.Consequence: In the event of a crash, if the windshield separates from the vehicle, it can increase the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will notify owners, and dealers will remove and reinstall the windshield, free of charge.  The recall began April 16, 2021.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 21C06.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2022 Super Duty F-250, F-350, 2021 F-150, Expedition, and Lincoln Navigator vehicles.  The front-door side impact pressure sensor modules may have been damaged during supplier assembly, which can cause the side impact air bags to not deploy properly in a crash.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 214, "Side Impact Protection."
recalls.Consequence: An air bag that does not deploy properly during a crash increases the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the driver and passenger front door side impact sensors, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed November 3, 2021.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 21C26.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles.  The electronic brake booster may leak brake fluid into the electronic control unit, which could result in reduced braking performance.
recalls.Consequence: Reduced braking performance can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the electronic brake booster assembly, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on July 28, 2021.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 21S33.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 Super Cab vehicles.  The front seatbelt webbing may be incorrectly routed.
recalls.Consequence: A misrouted seatbelt may not adequately restrain an occupant in a crash, increasing the risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Owners are advised to perform a preliminary self-inspection of the front seatbelts.  If the passenger-side seatbelt fails inspection, owners should not use the passenger seat until the repair is performed.  If the driver-side seatbelt fails inspection, owners should not drive their vehicle until the repair is performed.  Dealers will inspect the front seatbelts and, if the webbing is misrouted, will replace the seatbelt retractor and pretensioner, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on October 14, 2021.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 21C20.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles.  The two-piece driveshafts may have been improperly assembled, which could result in driveshaft separation.
recalls.Consequence: Driveshaft separation may result in a sudden loss of drive power, or unintended vehicle movement if the vehicle is in park without the parking brake applied, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect the driveshaft, and replace it if necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on June 15, 2021.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 21S25.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Component: STEERING:GEAR BOX (OTHER THAN RACK AND PINION)
recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles.  The steering gear may have internal damage, which could result in difficulty steering, or the inability to rotate the steering wheel while driving.
recalls.Consequence: Loss of steering control can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Owners are advised to not drive their vehicles until the repair is complete.  Vehicles will be towed in for service, and dealers will remove and replace the steering gear, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on June 4, 2021. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 21S28.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles.  The front windshield wiper motor may become inoperative, causing the wipers to fail.
recalls.Consequence: Inoperative windshield wipers can reduce visibility in certain conditions, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the front windshield wiper motor, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed June 22, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S12.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Component: ELECTRICAL SYSTEM: INTEGRATED TRAILER BRAKE CONTROL
recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150, 2022 Maverick, Expedition, Lincoln Navigator, F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 vehicles.  Due to a software error, a towed trailer equipped with an electric or electric-over hydraulic brake system may not brake.
recalls.Consequence: Loss of trailer brake functionality could result in extended stopping distance, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the integrated trailer brake control module software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 22, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S17.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles.  The Diagnostic Trouble Code (DTC) for low transmission fluid pressure may falsely activate and cause the transmission to unexpectedly shift into neutral.
recalls.Consequence: An unexpected shift into neutral will cause a loss of drive power and increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the Powertrain Control Module (PCM) software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on April 12, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S15.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2020-2021 F-150, Expedition, 2020-2022 Super Duty F-250, F-350, F-450, F-550, and 2020-2021 Lincoln Navigator vehicles.  The windshield wiper arms may break, causing the windshield wipers to fail.
recalls.Consequence: Inoperative windshield wipers can reduce visibility in certain driving conditions, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace both front windshield wiper arms, free of charge.  Interim owner notification letters, informing owners of the safety risk, were mailed on May 24, 2022.  Remedy parts are expected to be available 3rd Quarter 2022.  Owner notification letters were mailed on October 21, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S26.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling one 2021 F-150 vehicle.  A single vehicle may have been assembled without a fuel tank front attachment resulting in an unsecured fuel tank attachment strap.
recalls.Consequence: An improperly attached fuel tank increases the risk of a fuel leak and potential for fire.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair (if necessary) the fuel tank strap bracket, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed July 1, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S42.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150 vehicles.  Underbody heat and noise insulators may loosen and contact the aluminum driveshaft, which could damage the driveshaft and cause it to fracture.
recalls.Consequence: A fractured driveshaft can cause a loss of drive power, or a loss of vehicle control if the driveshaft contacts the ground.  Additionally, unintended movement could occur while parked if the parking brake is not engaged.  Any of these scenarios increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair the driveshaft, as necessary, and properly attach the underbody insulators, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed September 1, 2022.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S53.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150 vehicles.  The front windshield wiper motor may become inoperative, causing the wipers to fail.
recalls.Consequence: Inoperative windshield wipers can reduce visibility in certain conditions, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the front windshield wiper motor, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed June 30, 2023.  Remedy parts are expected in the 3rd Quarter of 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 22S71.  This recall expands previous recall number 22V-142.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles.  The windshield wiper arms may break, causing the windshield wipers to fail.
recalls.Consequence: Inoperative windshield wipers can reduce visibility in certain conditions, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and replace the wiper arms, as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed December 13, 2023.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S10.  This recall expands previous recall number 22V-250.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2023 F-150 vehicles equipped with a single exhaust system.  Contact with the rear axle housing may damage the wiring harness, causing the electric parking brake to activate unexpectedly.
recalls.Consequence: Unexpected activation of the electric parking brake while driving increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will install a protective tie strap, tape wrap, and replace the harness as necessary, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed February 12, 2024.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S35.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2023 F-150 vehicles equipped with the Trailer Tow Max Duty package and a 9.75-inch heavy duty axle with a 3/4 float axle design.  The rear axle hub bolt may fatigue and break, which can result in damage to the axle hub splines.
recalls.Consequence: Damaged axle hub splines can result in a vehicle rollaway when the vehicle is in park without the parking brake applied or cause a loss of drive power.  Both of these conditions can increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will replace the left and right rear axle shaft assemblies, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on May 9, 2025.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 23S65.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles equipped with the Onboard Scales feature.  An over-the-air software update to the body control module (BCM) may have disabled both reverse lights.
recalls.Consequence: Disabled reverse lights cannot alert others that the vehicle is reversing, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the body control module software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters are were mailed June 26, 2024.   Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 24S38.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Component: ENGINE AND ENGINE COOLING:ENGINE:HARD PARTS INTERNAL/MECHANICAL
recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 Bronco, F-150, Edge, Explorer, Lincoln Nautilus, and Lincoln Aviator vehicles equipped with either a 2.7L or 3.0L Nano EcoBoost engine.  The engine intake valves may break while driving, which can result in engine failure and a loss of drive power.
recalls.Consequence: A loss of drive power increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will perform an engine cycle test and replace the engine as necessary, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed July 3, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 24S55.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2020-2025 Explorer, Lincoln Aviator, 2020-2024 Escape, Lincoln Corsair, 2018-2024 F-150, Expedition and Lincoln Navigator vehicles.  The air bag warning label may be missing from the dashboard.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirement Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 208, "Occupant Crash Protection."
recalls.Consequence: Without a label that shows the proper restraint usage guidelines, the occupants may have an increased risk of injury in the event of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Ford will mail owners the warning labels, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed December 19, 2024.  Owners may call Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 24C39.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Component: ELECTRICAL SYSTEM: INTEGRATED TRAILER BRAKE CONTROL
recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 F-150, 2022 Maverick, Expedition, Lincoln Navigator, F-250, F-350, F-450, and F-550 vehicles previously repaired incorrectly under recall number 22V-193.  Due to a software error, a towed trailer equipped with an electric or electric-over hydraulic brake system may not brake.
recalls.Consequence: Loss of trailer brake functionality can extend the distance required to stop, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the integrated trailer brake control module software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 11, 2025.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 25S18.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 888-327-4236 (TTY 888-275-9171) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles previously repaired incorrectly under recall number 22V-188.  The Diagnostic Trouble Code (DTC) for low transmission fluid pressure may falsely activate and cause the transmission to unexpectedly shift into neutral.
recalls.Consequence: An unexpected shift into neutral will cause a loss of drive power and increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the Powertrain Control Module (PCM) software, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 22, 2025.  Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332.  Ford's number for this recall is 25S24.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 888-327-4236 (TTY 888-275-9171) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2024 Bronco, F-150, 2021-2024 Edge, 2022-2025 Escape, F-250, F-350, F-450, F-550, F-600, 2022-2024 Expedition, 2022-2025 Transit, 2021-2023 Mach-E, 2024 Ranger, Mustang, 2021-2023 Lincoln Nautilus, 2022-2024 Navigator, and 2023-2024 Corsair vehicles. A software error may cause the rearview camera image to delay, freeze, or not display when the vehicle is in reverse.
recalls.Consequence: A frozen or missing rearview camera image can reduce the driver's view behind the vehicle, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: The accessory protocol interface module (APIM) software will be updated by a dealer or through an over-the-air update, free of charge. This will be a phased campaign, with the remedy becoming available in different phases based on model and model years. Interim letters notifying owners of the safety risk were mailed on June 26, 2025. Additional letters will be mailed once the final remedy is available on each phase. Owner notification letters were sent on October 8, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25S49.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 888-327-4236 (TTY 888-275-9171) or go to nhtsa.gov.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021 F-150 vehicles equipped with the Onboard Scales feature that were repaired incorrectly under recall 24V443. An over-the-air software update to the body control module (BCM) may have disabled both reverse lights.
recalls.Consequence: Inoperative reverse lights may fail to alert others that the vehicle is reversing, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will update the body control module software, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed on June 27, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25S57.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2023 Bronco, Explorer, Lincoln Aviator, F-250 SD, F-350 SD, F-450 SD,  F-550 SD, 2021-2022 Lincoln Navigator, Mustang, F-150, and 2022 Expedition vehicles. The low-pressure fuel pump may fail, which can result in an engine stall while driving.
recalls.Consequence: An engine stall increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: The remedy is under development. Interim notification letters notifying owners of the safety risk were mailed July 16, 2025. Second letters will be sent once the remedy is available, anticipated March 2026. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25S75.

recalls.Summary: Ford Motor Company (Ford) is recalling certain 2021-2022 Expedition, Lincoln Navigator, 2021-2023 F-150, 2022 F-250 SD, F-350 SD, and F-450 SD vehicles. The moonroof wind deflector clips may be inadequately attached to the moonroof frame, which can result in the wind deflector detaching from the vehicle.
recalls.Consequence: A detached wind deflector can become a road hazard and increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Dealers will inspect and repair the  moonroof wind deflector as necessary, free of charge. Owner notification letters were mailed November 10, 2025. Owners may contact Ford customer service at 1-866-436-7332. Ford's number for this recall is 25SB7. Vehicle Identification Numbers (VINs) involved in this recall will be searchable on NHTSA.gov beginning October 30, 2025.

issues.title: 3.5L EcoBoost Engine Timing Chain Stretch
issues.description: The 3.5L EcoBoost V6 engine experiences timing chain stretch, leading to engine knock, reduced performance, and potential catastrophic engine damage if not addressed
issues.fix_description: Replace timing chains, guides, tensioners, and associated components. Often requires engine removal
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper viscosity, avoid aggressive driving during cold starts

issues.title: Fox Racing Shox Leakage
issues.description: Front and rear Fox Racing shocks develop seal leaks, causing reduced damping performance and oil stains on garage floors
issues.fix_description: Replace shock seals or entire shock units depending on damage extent
issues.prevention: Avoid excessive heat buildup, regular inspection, proper maintenance intervals

issues.title: Transmission Harsh Shifting and Slipping
issues.description: 10R80 transmission exhibits harsh shifts, delayed engagement, and occasional slipping, particularly in Sport and Baja modes
issues.fix_description: Software updates, transmission fluid changes, or complete transmission replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive driving until warmed up

issues.title: Intercooler Condensation and Boost Loss
issues.description: Intercooler accumulates excessive condensation causing power loss, rough running, and potential hydro-lock in extreme cases
issues.fix_description: Drain intercooler condensation, install aftermarket drain valve, or replace intercooler
issues.prevention: Regular intercooler drainage, avoid short trips in humid conditions

issues.title: Infotainment System SYNC 4 Freezing
issues.description: SYNC 4 infotainment system freezes, becomes unresponsive, or randomly reboots during operation
issues.fix_description: Software updates, system reset, or APIM module replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid using system during startup

issues.title: Brake Pedal Vibration and Pulsation
issues.description: Front brake rotors warp prematurely causing brake pedal pulsation and vibration during braking
issues.fix_description: Replace brake rotors and pads, ensure proper torque specifications
issues.prevention: Proper break-in procedure, avoid overheating brakes, regular inspection

issues.title: Exhaust System Cracking
issues.description: Exhaust pipes and components develop cracks near welds and joints, causing exhaust leaks and increased noise
issues.fix_description: Weld repairs or replace affected exhaust sections
issues.prevention: Regular inspection, avoid excessive heat cycles, proper mounting

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: In-tank fuel pump fails prematurely causing fuel starvation, stalling, and no-start conditions
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly and fuel filter
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank above 1/4 full, use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Cam Phaser Rattle
issues.description: Variable cam timing (VCT) phasers develop internal wear causing rattling noise on startup and reduced engine performance
issues.fix_description: Replace cam phasers, timing chains, and update engine software
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper specification, avoid extended idle periods

issues.title: Door Handle Paint Peeling
issues.description: Exterior door handles experience paint peeling and chipping, particularly on frequently used driver's side
issues.fix_description: Sand, prime, and repaint handles or replace door handle assemblies
issues.prevention: Regular waxing, avoid harsh chemicals, gentle handling

issues.title: Moonroof Drain Tube Clogging
issues.description: Sunroof drain tubes become clogged with debris causing water leaks into cabin and potential electrical damage
issues.fix_description: Clear drain tubes with compressed air or snake, replace if damaged
issues.prevention: Regular cleaning of sunroof area, avoid parking under trees

issues.title: Wheel Bearing Premature Failure
issues.description: Front wheel bearings fail prematurely, particularly on vehicles used for off-road driving, causing noise and handling issues
issues.prevention: Avoid deep water crossings, regular inspection, proper torque on lug nuts

editorial.hero_blurb: The F-150 Raptor transforms America's best-selling truck into a Baja-bred desert missile. With 450 horsepower of twin-turbo EcoBoost fury and FOX Racing shocks, it's equally at home bombing through sand dunes or hauling weekend gear.
editorial.essence: The Raptor is Ford's ultimate expression of high-speed off-road capability wrapped in pickup truck practicality. It's a genuine desert racer that can tow your boat, combining serious performance hardware with everyday usability that no dedicated off-road vehicle can match.
editorial.heritage: Born from Ford's SVT Raptor program in 2009, the nameplate draws inspiration from Ford's Baja racing success and the original Lightning performance trucks. The current generation launched in 2017 marked a shift from V8 power to twin-turbo V6 efficiency without sacrificing capability.
editorial.design_philosophy: Ford SVT designed the Raptor as a no-compromise desert racing machine that retains full pickup truck functionality. Every element serves dual purposes - aggressive styling that aids aerodynamics, wide fender flares that house massive tires, and a reinforced frame that handles both payload and punishment.
editorial.motorsport_history: The Raptor's DNA stems from Ford's factory Baja 1000 racing efforts and trophy truck development. Ford Performance continues using Raptor as a testbed for high-speed off-road technology, with lessons learned feeding directly back into production models.
editorial.engine_character: The 3.5L twin-turbo EcoBoost delivers brutal low-end torque with a surprisingly refined character. Peak torque arrives early and stays strong, providing effortless acceleration that belies the truck's 6,000-pound curb weight with a distinctly modern turbocharged personality.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 10-speed automatic is calibrated for aggressive response, with quick downshifts under throttle and intuitive behavior in sand and rock crawling modes. Paddle shifters provide manual control when precision is needed, though the automatic logic rarely needs intervention.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: FOX Racing 3.0 internal bypass shocks with position-sensitive damping provide exceptional high-speed control while maintaining comfort. The chassis feels planted and composed at speeds that would unsettle lesser trucks, with remarkable body control over rough terrain.
editorial.steering_feel: Electric power steering offers surprising feedback for a large truck, with good on-center feel and progressive weight build-up. Off-road, it filters out harsh impacts while maintaining connection to the front wheels' grip levels.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive Brembo front brakes provide strong, fade-resistant stopping power even when loaded. Pedal feel is firm and progressive, inspiring confidence whether hauling down a mountain grade or scrubbing speed before a desert wash.
editorial.sound_signature: The twin-turbo V6 produces a purposeful growl with subtle turbo whoosh under acceleration. It's more refined than the old V8 but still distinctly muscular, with exhaust notes that complement rather than overwhelm the driving experience.
editorial.ideal_owner: Adventure seekers who need genuine capability combined with daily usability, weekend warriors who tow boats or trailers to remote locations, and enthusiasts who appreciate cutting-edge off-road technology in a practical package.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Pure street performance enthusiasts seeking sports car dynamics, buyers prioritizing maximum fuel economy, or those who prefer traditional naturally aspirated V8 character over modern turbo efficiency.
editorial.buyers_summary: The 2021-2024 Raptor represents the sweet spot of the current generation, with refined powertrains and improved technology. Focus on examples with documented maintenance, as the turbo V6 rewards proper care, and consider the extensive option packages that significantly enhance capability.
cons: Higher maintenance costs than standard F-150

SETTING: Private collector's industrial warehouse garage. Brick warehouse with arched windows OR modern concrete gallery OR vintage factory with timber beams.

COMPOSITION: Front 3/4 hero angle showing front fascia and driver's side profile. Show COMPLETE car (all four wheels, both bumpers, full roofline). Camera at knee height.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
